<div id="review_280822314" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/280822314" />
    <a title="John Strohm" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4578166-john-strohm"><img alt="John Strohm" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1290604194p2/4578166.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/280822314?book_show_action=true">Feb 20, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="John Strohm" class="user" itemprop="url" name="John Strohm" href="/user/show/4578166-john-strohm">John Strohm</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer280822314" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12787018740819417386"><br/>Listened to the audiobook. 2 stars for the book, one for the audio production.<br/><br/>First, the audio production: After the excellent production of Ender&apos;s Shadow, this book returns with the same actors, but gets everything wrong. The volume is too soft. Many of the actors mispronounce &quot;hegemon&quot; and in some places this is crudely dubbed over by a different actor! Achilles&apos; name is pronounced inconsistently throughout. The music is terrible and too long. Overall, it sounds like a high school project and</span>
  <span id="freeText12787018740819417386" style="display:none"><br />Listened to the audiobook. 2 stars for the book, one for the audio production.<br /><br />First, the audio production: After the excellent production of Ender's Shadow, this book returns with the same actors, but gets everything wrong. The volume is too soft. Many of the actors mispronounce "hegemon" and in some places this is crudely dubbed over by a different actor! Achilles' name is pronounced inconsistently throughout. The music is terrible and too long. Overall, it sounds like a high school project and not a professional work.<br /><br />Now, onto the book. I loved Ender's Shadow. Shadow of the Hegemon was far weaker. The plot made little sense, and the characters say contradictory things. First they say that experience doesn't matter, just brains, and then they talk about how a lack of experience is fatal. While I was willing to suspend disbelief that a bunch of kids could be entrusted to battle the buggers, getting involved in geopolitics is too far-fetched.<br /><br />Card's diatribes on religion and morals get annoying in this book. Characters don't talk to each other, they make speeches at each other.<br /><br />Finally, the book doesn't end so much as hit "pause" and make you read the next one. No thanks.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12787018740819417386" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
